WEBVTT

00:00:07.040 --> 00:00:09.230
{\an9}Special Week

00:00:09.230 --> 00:00:11.690
{\an9}Silence Suzuka

00:00:12.070 --> 00:00:13.770
Spe-chan, the milk!

00:00:15.970 --> 00:00:16.900
<i>But…</i>

00:00:17.540 --> 00:00:19.060
<i>I want to win the next chance I get.</i>

00:00:23.210 --> 00:00:24.620
Spe-chan, your thumb!

00:00:30.130 --> 00:00:31.450
<i>I have to work harder.</i>

00:00:50.780 --> 00:00:52.780
No way!

00:00:53.990 --> 00:00:55.230
Spe-chan…

00:01:01.760 --> 00:01:06.980
Do you hear the fanfare as
we race towards the finish?

00:01:06.980 --> 00:01:13.510
I want to see that shining future with you

00:01:15.550 --> 00:01:21.850
{\an8}Umamusume

00:01:17.430 --> 00:01:21.720
{\an8}Pretty Derby

00:01:23.740 --> 00:01:29.460
If we just start to run, that's
where our story will begin

00:01:29.460 --> 00:01:34.480
It's always waiting right in front of us

00:01:34.480 --> 00:01:40.090
If you reach out just a little
more, we can seize that glory

00:01:40.090 --> 00:01:46.950
Aim for the top, challenge
them all, and it's off to the races

00:01:47.760 --> 00:01:52.950
Even the goddess of victory will be dazzled

00:01:52.950 --> 00:02:00.230
By your big debut that's just around the bend

00:02:00.230 --> 00:02:05.650
So can you hear the fanfare
as we race towards the finish?

00:02:05.650 --> 00:02:11.120
I want to see that shining future with you

00:02:11.120 --> 00:02:16.630
Let's overtake them all! It's
a track laid out just for you!

00:02:16.630 --> 00:02:24.390
Your dreams are at the finish if you believe

00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:30.000
{\an8}Race 4

00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:30.000
{\an8}Special Training!

00:02:30.310 --> 00:02:37.970
Derby. Turf. 2,400.

00:02:38.350 --> 00:02:41.970
Derby. Turf. 2,400.

00:02:39.770 --> 00:02:42.700
{\an8}<i>You're going to beat Seiun Sky
in the Japan Derby.</i>

00:02:42.700 --> 00:02:44.810
Use your loss to get stronger.

00:02:44.810 --> 00:02:45.640
Understood?

00:02:45.640 --> 00:02:46.770
Yes!

00:02:49.190 --> 00:02:51.400
Ow…

00:02:50.010 --> 00:02:51.400
{\an8}I'm sorry about that.

00:02:51.400 --> 00:02:52.190
Hey!

00:02:52.730 --> 00:02:54.430
Are you okay?

00:02:54.430 --> 00:02:56.110
Oh, I'm fine.

00:02:56.110 --> 00:02:57.740
Please take this as a token of my apology.

00:02:57.740 --> 00:02:59.780
D-Don't worry about it.

00:02:59.780 --> 00:03:02.260
Bye!

00:03:02.260 --> 00:03:05.370
Horse girls are really fast.

00:03:06.180 --> 00:03:08.850
{\an8}Grass Wonder

00:03:06.330 --> 00:03:10.180
Spe-chan, you're training so hard
for the Derby.

00:03:10.180 --> 00:03:12.790
As a result, she's not really
paying attention in class.

00:03:10.180 --> 00:03:12.600
{\an8}Seiun Sky

00:03:12.790 --> 00:03:16.420
I guess I'm not either, though.

00:03:14.790 --> 00:03:16.420
{\an5}Derby

00:03:16.420 --> 00:03:20.270
The other day, she was so busy
thinking about something else,

00:03:16.460 --> 00:03:19.150
{\an9}El Condor Pasa

00:03:20.270 --> 00:03:22.380
she ran into a pole,
and then apologized to it.

00:03:22.380 --> 00:03:24.030
Y-You saw that?

00:03:25.260 --> 00:03:27.380
You're such a scatterbrain.

00:03:27.380 --> 00:03:30.900
El-chan, stop embarrassing me…

00:03:28.970 --> 00:03:30.900
{\an8}She has less rice today.

00:03:30.900 --> 00:03:32.440
I'm back!

00:03:34.100 --> 00:03:35.260
Oh my.

00:03:35.260 --> 00:03:36.520
Welcome back.

00:03:36.520 --> 00:03:38.010
Urara-chan?

00:03:38.710 --> 00:03:41.280
I went and had my debut in Kouchi.

00:03:38.710 --> 00:03:41.280
{\an8}Haru Urara

00:03:41.280 --> 00:03:43.910
Kouchi was really nice.

00:03:42.550 --> 00:03:43.910
{\an5}Tosa

00:03:43.910 --> 00:03:46.530
Food tastes great after a trip.

00:03:46.900 --> 00:03:49.180
I feel great!

00:03:47.760 --> 00:03:49.180
{\an5}Tosa
Katsurahama

00:03:49.180 --> 00:03:52.040
The dawn of Japan grows near!

00:03:52.380 --> 00:03:54.880
It feels nice to race, doesn't it?

00:03:55.270 --> 00:03:57.450
Your debut race…

00:03:57.450 --> 00:03:58.710
Did you…

00:03:58.710 --> 00:04:01.050
Yeah, I managed to come in 5th!

00:04:01.050 --> 00:04:04.620
The audience liked me
because I tried my best.

00:04:04.620 --> 00:04:06.820
They told me "good luck"!

00:04:06.820 --> 00:04:09.070
I want to run again!

00:04:09.070 --> 00:04:10.770
Urara-chan…

00:04:11.340 --> 00:04:14.190
I need to work hard at rehab.

00:04:14.190 --> 00:04:15.520
Yeah.

00:04:16.590 --> 00:04:18.560
I just want to sleep.

00:04:18.560 --> 00:04:22.410
Yeah, but you were amazing
in the Satsukishou.

00:04:22.410 --> 00:04:24.820
Nah… maybe.

00:04:25.160 --> 00:04:26.700
I'm not going to lose next time.

00:04:27.060 --> 00:04:29.990
Hmm? I'm not sure about that.

00:04:29.990 --> 00:04:32.310
El-chan, what race are you running next?

00:04:32.310 --> 00:04:34.460
<i>This horse girl has never known loss.</i>

00:04:35.330 --> 00:04:36.370
<i>Four races, four wins.</i>

00:04:35.600 --> 00:04:40.210
{\an8}4 Races, 4 Wins

00:04:36.370 --> 00:04:40.210
<i>The strongest horse girl there is
will beat them all.</i>

00:04:36.600 --> 00:04:40.210
{\an8}The Strongest Horse Girl

00:04:40.700 --> 00:04:42.560
<i>The NHK Mile Cup.</i>

00:04:42.560 --> 00:04:44.410
<i>Like a bird dancing above the turf:</i>

00:04:44.410 --> 00:04:46.660
<i>El Condor Pasa will be participating.</i>

00:04:46.660 --> 00:04:48.850
I'm going to win, too.

00:04:46.660 --> 00:04:48.850
{\an8}NHK Mile Cup

00:04:49.850 --> 00:04:52.470
I'm going to win, too!

00:05:00.110 --> 00:05:03.070
All right. Let's take a break
at that park over there.

00:05:03.580 --> 00:05:06.250
You sure are breathing heavy.

00:05:06.250 --> 00:05:08.170
And you're sweating a lot.

00:05:08.170 --> 00:05:09.780
What was that?

00:05:09.780 --> 00:05:12.910
Don't yell out of nowhere.

00:05:10.220 --> 00:05:12.640
{\an7}Gold Ship

00:05:10.220 --> 00:05:12.640
{\an8}Vodka

00:05:10.220 --> 00:05:12.640
{\an9}Daiwa Scarlet

00:05:12.910 --> 00:05:15.250
They have taiyaki!

00:05:12.910 --> 00:05:15.250
{\an8}Taiyaki

00:05:17.860 --> 00:05:20.220
Guess I'll get some for you guys.

00:05:20.220 --> 00:05:21.710
Yay!

00:05:21.710 --> 00:05:23.050
I'll have a hot dog mayonnaise taiyaki.

00:05:21.710 --> 00:05:25.340
{\an8}Delicious Taiyaki

00:05:21.710 --> 00:05:25.340
{\an9}Taiyaki

00:05:23.050 --> 00:05:25.820
What? Taiyaki is best with shiroan.

00:05:25.820 --> 00:05:27.630
I'll have custard!

00:05:27.630 --> 00:05:30.050
What's this "secret" thing?

00:05:30.050 --> 00:05:33.210
Well, it's a secret.

00:05:33.210 --> 00:05:35.100
Give me ten of them.

00:05:35.100 --> 00:05:37.390
I'll have one with koshian.

00:05:37.390 --> 00:05:38.940
What do you want, Spe-chan?

00:05:38.940 --> 00:05:41.110
I'm good…

00:05:41.540 --> 00:05:42.420
What's wrong?

00:05:42.420 --> 00:05:44.570
Spe, you should eat.

00:05:44.570 --> 00:05:48.220
It's basically a miracle that our
stingy trainer would get us something.

00:05:48.220 --> 00:05:49.490
Stingy…

00:05:49.490 --> 00:05:52.460
Spe-chan, you haven't been
eating lately, right?

00:05:53.990 --> 00:05:56.140
You're on a diet?

00:05:56.140 --> 00:06:01.200
Yeah, I couldn't get the hook on
my nice dress to close at the Satsukishou.

00:06:01.200 --> 00:06:02.960
So I thought maybe I needed to…

00:06:02.960 --> 00:06:05.300
I mean, I realized that…

00:06:05.300 --> 00:06:07.220
You went up <i>[censored]</i> kilos, right?

00:06:07.220 --> 00:06:09.230
How did you know?

00:06:09.230 --> 00:06:11.300
I can tell just by looking at you.

00:06:11.300 --> 00:06:12.790
People normally can't do that!

00:06:12.790 --> 00:06:15.800
It's not necessarily a bad
thing to put on weight.

00:06:15.800 --> 00:06:19.330
It proves your body is putting things
in place so you can run faster.

00:06:19.330 --> 00:06:23.620
It's better that you eat a lot and put
on muscle so you can get stronger.

00:06:23.620 --> 00:06:24.150
But…!

00:06:25.250 --> 00:06:27.470
You're not convinced, huh?

00:06:28.100 --> 00:06:30.730
I want to do everything I can.

00:06:30.730 --> 00:06:35.830
Well, there's nothing wrong with lowering
your weight and putting on muscle.

00:06:35.830 --> 00:06:36.870
But…

00:06:37.700 --> 00:06:39.250
Especially in your legs.

00:06:40.010 --> 00:06:41.080
Hey!

00:06:41.080 --> 00:06:44.390
Why are you trying to sound serious when
you're really trying to be a pervert?!

00:06:44.390 --> 00:06:47.340
Spe-senpai, we'll help you with your diet!

00:06:47.340 --> 00:06:48.500
Really?

00:06:48.500 --> 00:06:51.340
You should let us help you once in a while.

00:06:52.230 --> 00:06:53.270
You guys…

00:06:54.660 --> 00:06:55.890
Thank you!

00:06:55.890 --> 00:06:57.810
This is fun!

00:06:55.930 --> 00:06:58.370
{\an8}Tokai Teio

00:06:57.810 --> 00:07:00.100
So what was the secret flavor?

00:07:00.100 --> 00:07:01.490
Let me try some.

00:07:02.860 --> 00:07:03.740
Hot mustard.

00:07:05.370 --> 00:07:11.110
Fight! Fight!

00:07:07.390 --> 00:07:09.210
Ow…

00:07:09.210 --> 00:07:11.110
They don't hold back, huh?

00:07:11.480 --> 00:07:13.990
I wonder if Spe-chan will be okay.

00:07:13.990 --> 00:07:18.310
Well, it's probably best if Spe goes out
and has fun with them for a change of pace.

00:07:18.810 --> 00:07:21.910
If you get stuck worrying about things,
you won't be able to move forward.

00:07:21.910 --> 00:07:25.440
Anyway, Suzuka, about your next race…

00:07:25.440 --> 00:07:27.420
I'm having you participate
in the fall Tennoushou.

00:07:27.820 --> 00:07:28.750
Okay.

00:07:28.750 --> 00:07:32.040
But before that, I'm going to have
you participate in the Mainichi Oukan.

00:07:32.040 --> 00:07:32.870
Okay.

00:07:32.870 --> 00:07:36.120
I'd also like to do the Takarazuka Kinen.

00:07:36.120 --> 00:07:36.930
Okay.

00:07:37.490 --> 00:07:41.720
Suzuka-san, can't you sound more interested?

00:07:41.720 --> 00:07:44.450
No matter which race it
is, nothing changes the fact

00:07:44.450 --> 00:07:46.940
that all I have to do
is run as fast as I can.

00:07:47.260 --> 00:07:49.240
Well, I guess that's true.

00:07:49.240 --> 00:07:52.860
Once the fall Tennoushou is over, you'll…

00:07:57.140 --> 00:07:59.870
<i>Mom, everyone's helping me,</i>

00:08:00.350 --> 00:08:02.870
<i>and I'm going to start special
training for the Derby.</i>

00:08:04.060 --> 00:08:06.000
You want me to…

00:08:06.000 --> 00:08:09.570
Yes, it's important to be hungry for a fight.

00:08:09.570 --> 00:08:10.990
You get rid of what you like,

00:08:10.990 --> 00:08:14.680
and tell yourself you're going
to get a treat if you win.

00:08:14.680 --> 00:08:16.970
B-Being hungry…

00:08:16.970 --> 00:08:19.970
Now, seal up those carrots!

00:08:29.500 --> 00:08:33.610
It's best to just exercise diligently
if you're going on a diet.

00:08:33.610 --> 00:08:35.460
Th-That makes sense.

00:08:35.460 --> 00:08:37.620
But what's up with that wooden sword?

00:08:37.620 --> 00:08:40.790
I'm going to give you some tough love!

00:08:42.580 --> 00:08:45.330
Now, it's time to start your
hellish muscle training!

00:08:45.750 --> 00:08:47.550
What?!

00:08:47.550 --> 00:08:48.810
One hundred sit-ups!

00:08:48.810 --> 00:08:50.420
O-Okay!

00:08:50.420 --> 00:08:51.620
One hundred back extensions!

00:08:51.620 --> 00:08:53.090
We're not done yet?!

00:08:53.090 --> 00:08:54.420
One hundred push-ups!

00:08:54.420 --> 00:08:55.340
Okay!

00:08:55.820 --> 00:08:57.940
One hundred high knees!

00:08:57.940 --> 00:09:00.140
Vodka-chan, forgive me!

00:09:00.140 --> 00:09:02.890
{\an8}Studio A

00:09:00.570 --> 00:09:02.890
Those two don't get it.

00:09:02.890 --> 00:09:04.970
You can't just be hard on
someone the whole time.

00:09:04.970 --> 00:09:06.650
It has to be fun.

00:09:06.650 --> 00:09:09.860
So, I'm going to teach you dancing.

00:09:11.070 --> 00:09:12.360
Okay!

00:09:12.830 --> 00:09:16.490
Spe-chan, make the same pose as me.

00:09:16.490 --> 00:09:18.280
L-Like this?

00:09:18.280 --> 00:09:19.410
No.

00:09:19.780 --> 00:09:22.270
Like this. And this.

00:09:22.870 --> 00:09:24.930
L-Like this?

00:09:24.930 --> 00:09:26.620
Come on, like this!

00:09:26.620 --> 00:09:28.810
You're going to be off balance

00:09:28.810 --> 00:09:30.310
and won't have fun dancing if you can't!

00:09:30.310 --> 00:09:32.760
We're practicing until you can do this!

00:09:32.760 --> 00:09:34.510
You're being hard on me, too!

00:09:37.710 --> 00:09:41.190
Spe, you can take off the blindfold!

00:09:46.060 --> 00:09:47.910
Being a horse girl is about guts!

00:09:47.910 --> 00:09:49.100
Jump off!

00:09:49.540 --> 00:09:52.440
Does this have anything to
do with being on a diet?

00:09:54.940 --> 00:09:57.310
If you're not going, I will.

00:09:57.310 --> 00:09:58.090
Huh?

00:09:58.090 --> 00:10:01.200
It's important to have guts when you need it.

00:10:05.100 --> 00:10:07.710
Come on, Spe! You don't want
to lose to her, do you?!

00:10:07.710 --> 00:10:08.750
Jump!

00:10:20.930 --> 00:10:23.740
No. No, I can't do this!

00:10:28.860 --> 00:10:30.660
Spe, that was hilarious!

00:10:30.660 --> 00:10:32.090
I'm moved!

00:10:35.420 --> 00:10:37.740
<i>Special Week has moved up from the outside.</i>

00:10:38.100 --> 00:10:39.830
{\an8}Will she make her move?!

00:10:38.950 --> 00:10:42.990
Seiun Sky was able to pull
out of the pack here…

00:10:42.990 --> 00:10:47.000
<i>Seiun Sky has pulled right ahead!</i>

00:10:47.000 --> 00:10:48.950
<i>Seiun Sky has taken the lead.</i>

00:10:48.950 --> 00:10:51.000
<i>King Halo is trying to catch up.</i>

00:10:51.000 --> 00:10:53.210
<i>Special Week is third!</i>

00:10:53.210 --> 00:10:54.630
<i>She's trying her best to get up that hill!</i>

00:10:54.630 --> 00:10:56.250
{\an8}Seiun Sky's still in the lead.

00:10:55.110 --> 00:10:57.960
Hmm…? What's this?

00:10:56.250 --> 00:10:57.960
{\an8}Special Week's having trouble.

00:10:57.960 --> 00:11:01.970
{\an6}Umamusume

00:10:57.960 --> 00:11:01.970
{\an6}Pretty Derby

00:11:12.230 --> 00:11:15.300
El Condor Pasa's in good shape.

00:11:15.300 --> 00:11:17.140
We're training. Get out.

00:11:17.140 --> 00:11:20.660
Wouldn't expect anything less from the
school's strongest team, Team Rigil.

00:11:20.660 --> 00:11:22.360
You're training hard.

00:11:22.360 --> 00:11:24.030
Of course.

00:11:24.030 --> 00:11:26.990
Hana, here's a present for you.

00:11:28.910 --> 00:11:30.930
{\an8}Challenge Letter

00:11:29.550 --> 00:11:30.750
A challenge letter?

00:11:33.140 --> 00:11:34.470
A mock race?

00:11:34.470 --> 00:11:35.570
Yep.

00:11:35.570 --> 00:11:36.390
With who?

00:11:36.390 --> 00:11:38.260
Her.

00:11:38.260 --> 00:11:39.130
You mean…

00:11:39.510 --> 00:11:40.790
Taiki Shuttle?

00:11:43.940 --> 00:11:46.890
That's what they mean
when they say "fast as lightning."

00:11:47.670 --> 00:11:52.260
I think you know this, but she's the fastest
short-distance horse girl in Japan.

00:11:52.260 --> 00:11:53.530
Yep.

00:11:53.530 --> 00:11:55.400
That's why I want her to see what it's like.

00:11:55.400 --> 00:11:57.150
Special Week.

00:11:57.150 --> 00:11:58.940
Special Week?

00:11:58.940 --> 00:12:01.150
You mean from the Satsukishou?

00:12:01.550 --> 00:12:04.180
Please. There's no time.

00:12:06.200 --> 00:12:08.410
{\an8}Special Week

00:12:09.070 --> 00:12:10.200
Hana-san…

00:12:10.200 --> 00:12:11.620
Fine.

00:12:12.130 --> 00:12:13.870
I guess I'm in.

00:12:16.000 --> 00:12:19.250
{\an8}Congratulations! Mock Race!
Special Week
VS
Taiki Shuttle
(The fastest short-distance horse girl)

00:12:20.310 --> 00:12:22.760
Trainer-san, what's this about?

00:12:23.140 --> 00:12:24.020
Be glad!

00:12:24.020 --> 00:12:26.530
I set up a mock race for you.

00:12:26.530 --> 00:12:28.450
A mock race…

00:12:28.450 --> 00:12:29.930
You mean with Taiki Shuttle-san?!

00:12:30.280 --> 00:12:32.690
She won twice in a row during
last year's G-Is, right?

00:12:32.690 --> 00:12:36.150
The Mile Championship
and Sprinter's Stakes…

00:12:36.150 --> 00:12:37.140
She's good.

00:12:37.140 --> 00:12:39.330
She's the best opponent you could have.

00:12:39.330 --> 00:12:40.650
Spe-chan, you can do it!

00:12:43.090 --> 00:12:44.280
Suzuka-san?

00:12:44.870 --> 00:12:46.010
What's wrong?

00:12:46.010 --> 00:12:47.120
I'm against this.

00:12:47.470 --> 00:12:50.620
Suzuka-san… what's the matter?

00:12:56.260 --> 00:12:58.790
Spe-chan, you've put on weight.

00:12:59.670 --> 00:13:02.070
Your couldn't fit into your costume, right?

00:13:02.070 --> 00:13:03.940
And your weighed yourself…

00:13:03.940 --> 00:13:05.400
Suzuka-san!

00:13:05.400 --> 00:13:06.800
I'm worried about you.

00:13:07.120 --> 00:13:09.460
If you push yourself, you could get hurt.

00:13:09.890 --> 00:13:12.060
Also, if…

00:13:12.670 --> 00:13:17.810
<i>If you lose… If you start hating to run…</i>

00:13:17.810 --> 00:13:21.280
It's true that Taiki Shuttle is the
strongest short-distance runner.

00:13:21.280 --> 00:13:23.360
You might not be able to win.

00:13:24.020 --> 00:13:26.560
But the fastest way to get stronger

00:13:26.560 --> 00:13:30.210
is to go straight up against
someone stronger than you.

00:13:30.210 --> 00:13:32.490
Will I be able to get stronger?

00:13:32.490 --> 00:13:37.040
I think you can learn many times more
during the real thing than during training.

00:13:37.040 --> 00:13:39.670
Don't think about it, and just go run.

00:13:41.540 --> 00:13:42.350
Right!

00:13:43.630 --> 00:13:46.750
Suzuka-san, I'm going to try it.

00:13:51.770 --> 00:13:53.430
All right.

00:13:57.330 --> 00:14:00.510
Wow, this feels nice.

00:14:07.950 --> 00:14:11.090
It must be nice to be able to run here!

00:14:11.090 --> 00:14:13.930
{\an8}Yakisoba

00:14:11.500 --> 00:14:14.490
Special Spica Yakisoba here.
Anyone want some?

00:14:12.930 --> 00:14:14.490
{\an9}Oguri Cap

00:14:14.490 --> 00:14:16.450
You can do it!

00:14:23.150 --> 00:14:24.450
Suzuka-san…

00:14:47.020 --> 00:14:48.710
Could you sleep last night?

00:14:48.710 --> 00:14:51.820
Yeah. I'm a little nervous, though.

00:14:51.820 --> 00:14:54.700
Watch your opponent closely
and steal everything she has.

00:14:54.700 --> 00:14:56.290
It's short distance.

00:14:56.290 --> 00:14:58.970
It'll be over if you blink.

00:14:58.970 --> 00:14:59.960
Right!

00:14:59.960 --> 00:15:04.710
{\an6}Start

00:15:00.290 --> 00:15:02.890
Special Week, it's almost time.

00:15:03.380 --> 00:15:04.710
R-Right.

00:15:04.710 --> 00:15:06.530
I have to be the finish line…

00:15:06.530 --> 00:15:11.220
Why do I have to put up with this pain?

00:15:11.220 --> 00:15:14.930
{\an8}Finish

00:15:11.530 --> 00:15:14.930
Taiki Shuttle's going to win, anyway.

00:15:11.530 --> 00:15:13.930
{\an9}Hishi Amazon

00:15:17.490 --> 00:15:21.330
Th-Thank you for letting me practice
with you. I'll try my best!

00:15:21.330 --> 00:15:22.790
Howdy, y'all!

00:15:22.790 --> 00:15:23.480
Howdy?

00:15:23.880 --> 00:15:26.660
You gotta do everything with full power.

00:15:23.880 --> 00:15:26.650
{\an7}Taiki Shuttle

00:15:28.310 --> 00:15:29.130
Right!

00:15:35.700 --> 00:15:41.080
{\an8}Start

00:15:36.130 --> 00:15:41.080
We will now start this mock race,
Taiki Shuttle vs. Special Week.

00:15:36.130 --> 00:15:38.560
{\an7}Air Groove

00:15:47.090 --> 00:15:49.550
{\an8}Start

00:15:47.630 --> 00:15:48.510
Ready…

00:15:49.140 --> 00:15:49.670
Start!

00:15:50.700 --> 00:15:52.870
You can do it!

00:16:02.740 --> 00:16:04.400
<i>Sh-She's fast.</i>

00:16:07.770 --> 00:16:09.700
She's a G-I horse girl, all right.

00:16:09.700 --> 00:16:10.740
Amazing.

00:16:19.660 --> 00:16:21.790
<i>It's taking all I have
just to keep up with her.</i>

00:16:22.900 --> 00:16:23.670
<i>But…</i>

00:16:26.230 --> 00:16:29.840
<i>But it's kind of easy to run.</i>

00:16:34.130 --> 00:16:36.140
Not a bad idea.

00:16:36.140 --> 00:16:39.120
Is it okay for her to
stick so close behind her?

00:16:39.120 --> 00:16:41.070
It's called the slipstream.

00:16:41.070 --> 00:16:44.090
That's the place with the
least wind resistance.

00:16:44.090 --> 00:16:46.020
She's in a good spot.

00:16:54.700 --> 00:16:56.530
<i>I'm not getting as tired as I usually do.</i>

00:16:57.340 --> 00:16:58.530
<i>I might be able to win!</i>

00:17:22.180 --> 00:17:24.220
<i>I want to catch up to her.</i>

00:17:34.630 --> 00:17:36.780
It's too early to give up.

00:17:59.510 --> 00:18:00.800
<i>This rhythm…</i>

00:18:17.530 --> 00:18:18.660
That's it!

00:18:18.660 --> 00:18:19.730
What's it?!

00:18:19.730 --> 00:18:21.160
Spe-senpai's losing, though!

00:18:21.160 --> 00:18:23.580
Go! Crush her!

00:18:21.160 --> 00:18:23.580
{\an4}Special
Yakisoba

00:18:24.980 --> 00:18:27.330
Spe-chan's running differently now.

00:18:27.690 --> 00:18:30.170
<i>You tighten your stride, run smaller.</i>

00:18:30.170 --> 00:18:32.340
<i>Short-stride running.</i>

00:18:33.270 --> 00:18:35.340
<i>The hill should be a bit easier to run now.</i>

00:18:35.780 --> 00:18:37.760
I wonder if Spe-senpai can win.

00:18:37.760 --> 00:18:40.270
A fight is always 50-50.

00:18:41.010 --> 00:18:43.350
Horse girls need guts!

00:18:41.010 --> 00:18:43.350
{\an4}Special
Yakisoba

00:18:43.770 --> 00:18:45.350
Go!

00:18:55.890 --> 00:18:57.820
That's not happening!

00:19:08.580 --> 00:19:11.130
Spe-chan looks like she's having fun!

00:19:11.130 --> 00:19:12.960
I've found my rival.

00:19:22.970 --> 00:19:26.370
<i>Suzuka-san, I think I can win.</i>

00:19:26.970 --> 00:19:29.980
{\an8}Finish

00:19:29.010 --> 00:19:29.980
Amazon!

00:19:29.980 --> 00:19:31.140
{\an8}Start

00:19:30.290 --> 00:19:31.140
Amazon!

00:19:31.140 --> 00:19:34.460
Come on. Taiki Shuttle's going to win…

00:19:43.070 --> 00:19:45.200
F-Finish!

00:19:43.470 --> 00:19:45.200
{\an8}Finish

00:19:50.960 --> 00:19:53.830
{\an4}Finish

00:19:51.580 --> 00:19:54.600
{\an6}Start

00:19:51.610 --> 00:19:53.300
Why are you slacking off?!

00:19:53.300 --> 00:19:54.100
Oh no!

00:19:54.100 --> 00:19:54.920
Wait!

00:20:00.580 --> 00:20:02.350
<i>I lost again.</i>

00:20:04.350 --> 00:20:05.290
<i>But…</i>

00:20:18.500 --> 00:20:20.740
That was very exciting!

00:20:23.710 --> 00:20:27.140
Hey, you really showed me a lot out there!

00:20:27.660 --> 00:20:29.330
Thank you very much!

00:20:29.330 --> 00:20:31.910
Oh! You're so cute!

00:20:31.910 --> 00:20:34.500
Taiki Shuttle-san, I…

00:20:34.500 --> 00:20:36.500
{\an4}Special
Yakisoba

00:20:35.010 --> 00:20:36.500
Spe-chan!

00:20:43.700 --> 00:20:45.510
I kept my end of the bargain.

00:20:45.510 --> 00:20:47.800
Taiki Shuttle's fast.

00:20:47.800 --> 00:20:49.590
I told you.

00:20:50.010 --> 00:20:52.820
Next time, set up a mock race
that'll benefit me, instead.

00:20:54.180 --> 00:20:55.500
Thanks.

00:21:10.300 --> 00:21:12.190
Spe-chan, you look happy.

00:21:13.100 --> 00:21:14.960
I'm having fun every day.

00:21:15.610 --> 00:21:17.740
I mean, I'm losing, too.

00:21:18.210 --> 00:21:21.550
But it's fun spending time with everyone.

00:21:22.290 --> 00:21:23.550
I see.

00:21:24.050 --> 00:21:26.510
Suzuka-san, aren't you having fun?

00:21:26.510 --> 00:21:27.540
Me?

00:21:27.990 --> 00:21:29.100
I…

00:21:29.100 --> 00:21:31.010
Hey, it's started.

00:21:31.340 --> 00:21:33.930
<i>El Condor Pasa!</i>

00:21:33.930 --> 00:21:35.810
<i>She's taken the lead right away!</i>

00:21:35.810 --> 00:21:36.950
<i>A complete lead!</i>

00:21:36.950 --> 00:21:40.290
<i>She dominated the G-Is!</i>

00:21:40.290 --> 00:21:41.230
<i>She's strong!</i>

00:21:40.820 --> 00:21:42.530
El-chan's amazing!

00:21:41.230 --> 00:21:43.370
{\an8}One minute and 33.7 seconds!

00:21:42.530 --> 00:21:43.820
She really is!

00:21:43.370 --> 00:21:44.570
{\an8}Five races, five wins.

00:21:44.570 --> 00:21:46.740
{\an8}She's a G-I horse girl!

00:21:45.010 --> 00:21:46.130
Great work.

00:21:46.740 --> 00:21:48.730
That was some amazing running.

00:21:48.730 --> 00:21:50.320
Thank you.

00:21:50.320 --> 00:21:52.950
What will be your next race,
El Condor Pasa-san?

00:21:52.950 --> 00:21:57.370
In order to get her on the global stage,
she'll be running in the Japan Derby.

00:21:57.940 --> 00:21:59.920
El-chan's going to do the Derby, too?

00:22:01.110 --> 00:22:02.730
I thought this would happen.

00:22:02.730 --> 00:22:04.380
<i>El Condor Pasa-san,
please give us a statement.</i>

00:22:04.380 --> 00:22:07.260
I'm going to win in the Derby, too!

00:22:07.260 --> 00:22:09.890
Spe-chan, let's fight this one out!

00:22:09.890 --> 00:22:11.890
<i>Wait for me!</i>

00:22:11.890 --> 00:22:15.140
{\an8}I'm going to win, though!

00:22:12.550 --> 00:22:15.140
Guess it's not going to be an easy win.

00:22:19.730 --> 00:22:23.110
I-I'm going to take first place!

00:22:23.500 --> 00:22:24.980
Ow!

00:22:25.700 --> 00:22:28.770
In a dash, in a flash,
just a little more now,

00:22:28.770 --> 00:22:31.480
each new race like a dream neverending

00:22:31.480 --> 00:22:34.290
Every one of us will blaze a
trail aimed right for the stars

00:22:34.290 --> 00:22:39.460
Together we'll run! Let's
go! Our starting gate!

00:22:48.590 --> 00:22:53.920
With curiosity in hand, go tug
on tomorrow's tail and say hello

00:22:53.920 --> 00:22:58.920
It's right there, so go on and close
the gap now (Right here and now!)

00:22:59.630 --> 00:23:05.010
Can't play by the rules they tell
you! Gotta learn it all by experience!

00:23:05.010 --> 00:23:09.950
If we just plan to run for the
end, everything will turn out okay!

00:23:10.110 --> 00:23:13.980
Can't get me down,
hesitate, or go too slowly!

00:23:15.730 --> 00:23:19.700
We know that deep in our hearts is a song

00:23:19.780 --> 00:23:22.920
that sings "give it your all"! Make it shine!

00:23:23.500 --> 00:23:26.720
In a dash, in a flash, just a
little more now, (Dash! Dash!)

00:23:26.720 --> 00:23:29.470
every step like the wind
neverending (Zoom! Zoom!)

00:23:29.470 --> 00:23:32.370
A twinkling star that we wear
on our sleeves (But only one!)

00:23:32.370 --> 00:23:34.670
Let's let our hearts race
together as one! (Grow up! Shine!)

00:23:34.670 --> 00:23:37.800
One more step, one more push,
just a little more now, (Dash! Dash!)

00:23:37.800 --> 00:23:40.450
each new race like a dream
neverending (Zoom! Zoom!)

00:23:40.450 --> 00:23:43.300
Every one of us will see
our path to the very end!

00:23:43.300 --> 00:23:49.030
Let's run now, everyone!
Let's go! Our starting gate!

